# Licensing for editor-extensions/vscode/

While this directory lives in the contentRX monorepo it is governed by
the **root LICENSE** ([Functional Source License, FSL-1.1-MIT](../../LICENSE)),
not by the standalone MIT terms previously stated here. The VS Code
extension is part of the same source-available product as the engine,
web app, and other surfaces.

## Future intent

When this extension is published to the VS Code Marketplace as a
standalone artifact, the released VSIX ships under the **MIT
License** so external maintainers can fork, adapt, and contribute.
The in-monorepo source converts to MIT on the FSL "Future License"
date two years after each release.

Until that conversion, the FSL-1.1-MIT terms in the root LICENSE
govern this directory.

## Why this directory has its own LICENSE file

Reversibility insurance. This LICENSE file is the placeholder for the
plain MIT grant that activates on Marketplace publication. Don't
delete it.

